Foot-and-mouth disease, Namibia
-------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 3 Dec 2014 from Dr Albertina Shilongo, Deputy Chief Veterinary Officer, Division Epidemiology, Import/Export Control and Training, Directorate of Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture, Water & Forestry, Windhoek, Namibia

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 1 Dec 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 2 Dec 2014
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 15 Oct 2014
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: not typed
Nature of diagnosis: suspicion, clinical
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Linyati, Caprivi [Zambezi]
Date of start of the outbreak: 1 Dec 2014
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 470 / 9 / 0 / - / -

Affected population: Nine cattle from 3 kraals with a total herd of 470 head have oral and foot lesions suggestive of foot and mouth disease.
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 1.91 / 0 / 0 / **
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter
** Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comment: Nine cattle from 3 kraals with a population of 470 head have oral and foot lesions suggestive of foot and mouth disease. A containment area has been established with a 40-km radius zone around Linyati. A temporary but complete ban of all susceptible livestock movement within and into Caprivi Region was imposed with immediate effect. Surveillance and outbreak investigation teams are deployed in the affected area to establish the source and extent of the outbreak.

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine; movement control inside the country; screening; zoning; no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied: vaccination in response to the outbreak(s); disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); dipping/spraying

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.

